Add a Dynamic Interaction to a Widget

You can connect a user action to a dashboard action. For example, when you select a bar in an overview chart, a dashboard page with the details of the selection opens.

To edit the dashboard, click  and select the widget.
In the right panel, click Interaction.
Click Create Interaction.
Select the interaction.
For Event, select the type of action that triggers the interaction, such as selecting a row or clicking the widget.
You canâ€™t create a select event for a container, image, number, or text widget.

A widget can have multiple actions. When more than one action exists, the actions are performed sequentially when you click or select the item.

From the Action dropdown, select Navigate to.
For Link To, select the destination to link to, such as a dashboard, lens, or page.

Select the destination. The options are based on your Link To selection.
From the Action dropdown, select Return to Initial View, and then select Return to initial view for Reset.
Click Apply.
To test the interaction, preview the dashboard. Then save the dashboard.
title: Add a Dynamic Interaction to a CRM Analytics Dashboard Widget
